   "message": "<h2>Release notes for DiGidot C4 Firmware 2.1.3 - Released on 25-3-2020</h2>\n\n<h5>Added</h5>\n\n<ul>\n<li>UI: When a playlist is shuffled, the interface shows an icon in the playerbar below</li>\n<li>API: When starting scenes, you can now use the 'fade' parameter and a number in ms that applies to both fade in and out</li>\n<li>API: The 'list' command of scene now contains the 'unique_id' of the scene</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h5>Changed</h5>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Manual: The manual is now HTML based so that it's displayed correctly on every device type</li>\n<li>UI: Reworked text on some places</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h5>Improved</h5>\n\n<ul>\n<li>System: With this version, the logging capability is expanded so if there are any troubles with your C4, we can now have a better explanation and solution for it.</li>\n<li>System: Master determination process will start if there's no interface activity for 5 seconds</li>\n<li>System: Less memory needed for the 'output' command in some cases</li>\n<li>System: Logging syntax simplified to reduce the load</li>\n<li>SD-card: The controller is now capable of splitting large files on the SD-card internally so up to 256 scenes can now be shown at a time and triggers can be much larger now</li>\n<li>UI: Improved dark theme on some pages</li>\n<li>UI: Reduce the number of getting the state of the C4 to improve stability</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h5>Fixed</h5>\n\n<ul>\n<li>HSV: Removed any memory items leftovers from the HSV</li>\n<li>Sync: Fixed an overflow that could potentially mean that multiple controllers can be out of sync when playing the same scene</li>\n<li>Shuffle Playlist: The returned scene is now correct when shuffle is active</li>\n<li>Shuffle Playlist: If no specified value for the seed is given, an random number will be chosen</li>\n<li>Triggers: Analog triggers that are set to react on anything other then \"value\" are also triggered at startup.</li>\n<li>System: Greatly improved the C4 stability after 70 minutes of runtime</li>\n<li>IO: When editing universe numbers in the IOconfig, the second universe its first channel works properly again</li>\n<li>Scene: When a scene is corrupt, the C4 will no longer crash</li>\n<li>HSV: 16 bit IC's now works correctly with color adjustment (HSV)</li>\n<li>UI: Enable and disable triggers are now working correctly</li>\n<li>UI: Various fixes for the IOconfig page</li>\n<li>UI: on iOS, when generating a scene, the interface will no lag anymore</li>\n<li>UI: Fixed an issue when in some scenarios, the update process will hang</li>\n</ul>\n"
}